  "instructions": [
    "Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a clay or ceramic tagine over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion, ginger, and garlic and sauté until the onion is translucent.",
    "Add the cumin, coriander, cayenne pepper, and salt, and stir to combine.",
    "Add the soaked chickpeas, dark chocolate chips, and coconut milk, and stir to combine.",
    "Bring to a simmer and cook for 20 minutes, or until the flavors have melded together and the chickpeas are tender.",
    "Add the dum and stir to combine.",
    "Continue to cook for 5-10 minutes, or until the dum is heated through.",
    "Season with thyme and serve hot."
  ],
